 it would scratch some need, it would leave you fulfilled.

245
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,000
 And it tells us that the game of life is kind of like Monopoly.

246
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,000
 I mean, at the heart of the American dream is the idea that that game you played

247
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:56,000
 growing up, Monopoly, where you try to buy as much stuff as you can,

248
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,000
 and the winner at the end is the person who has the most.

249
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:02,000
 The Bible says that's not true at all.

250
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:06,000
 Jesus is going to tell us that life is a lot more like the game of Uno.

251
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:09,000
 You guys remember Uno? Your grandma plays Uno?

252
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 Most of you probably haven't played because you're not over 85,

253
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:17,000
 but Uno is this game where the winner is not who has the most cards,

254
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:21,000
 it's the one who gives or gets rid of the most.

255
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:26,000
 And Jesus is going to say, ultimately, life is not about acquiring and getting more.

256
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:31,000
 It is about giving more to the only kingdom that will last, which is Christ's.

257
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
 Don't live your life. Don't be foolish.

258
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 And he says this man was a fool because the American dream,

259
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:44,000
 if it's pursued at the extent of knowing God and making him known,

260
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
 it makes you a fool.

261
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:52,000
 And in inverse, living for eternity is the only thing that can make you full on the inside,

262
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,000
 like F-U-L-L.

263
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:58,000
 Living for the American dream makes you a fool.

264
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 But living for eternity is not just something that's going to have impact for eternity.

265
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:06,000
 It fills, it satisfies because you were made for it.

266
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 And Jesus looks into the eyes of this man and to his crowd and says,

267
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,000
 "Don't buy the lie that you're here to just acquire and acquire."

268
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:18,000
 There's a friend of mine who tells this story about the time his company went public,

269
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:21,000
 and he became a billionaire overnight.

270
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:25,000
 And he says, "There was a party in this hotel that we were at.

271
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:29,000
 It just went public. Everyone's downstairs. They're all celebrating.

272
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 And I just became a billionaire.

273
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:37,000
 And I went back up to my hotel room, and I started working again.

274
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:45,000
 And I wasn't following Jesus, I just wasn't able to be satisfied

275
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,000
 because he wasn't following Jesus.

276
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:53,000
 And even turning a billionaire overnight didn't satisfy

277
00:14:53,000 --> 00:15:01,000
 because there is no amount of wealth, status, success that can, but Jesus can.

278
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:05,000
 And Jesus says, "If you spend your life buying the lie the world around you sells,

279
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:09,000
 the American dream is what it's all about, you're a fool.

280
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:15,000
 And so am I. But if you spend your life living for eternity, it will make you full on the inside."

281
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:20,000
 And then he launches in to another challenge that pursuit of the American dream creates.

282
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 He says this, "And then he said to his disciples,

283
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:26,000
 'I tell you, do not worry about your life.'" He brings up anxiety,

284
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:31,000
 which is at the heart of, honestly, why a lot of us want to have and get more and have more in the bank.

285
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 "'What you will wear about what you eat or your body, what you will wear.

286
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
 For life is more than food and the body more than clothes.

287
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:42,000
 Consider the ravens. They do not sow or reap. They have no storeroom or barn, yet God feeds them.

288
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 Are you not more valuable than God?'" Translation, "God will provide for you."

289
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
 "'Who of you by worrying can add a single hour to your life?

290
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:55,000
 Do not, since you cannot do this very little thing, why do you worry about the rest?'"

291
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:58,000
 Brings up another illustration, "'Consider the flowers of the field.

292
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:02,000
 They don't labor or spend, I tell you, not even Solomon in all of his splendor was dressed like one of these.

293
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 If that's how God clothes the grass of the field which is here today and tomorrow is thrown in the fire,

294
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:10,000
 how much more will he clothe you? You of little faith.

295
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:15,000
 Do not set your heart on what you will eat or drink. Do not worry about it.

296
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:21,000
 For the pagans," those are people of the world, those are people who do not know God, he's saying,

297
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:27,000
 "'They run after all those things, and your Father knows you need them.

298
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 But seek his kingdom and these things will be given to you.'"

299
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,000
 What is Jesus saying? There's so much there, we don't have time to unpack, but he's driving home.

300
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,000
 "'You have a heavenly Father who will provide for you.'

301
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:41,000
 Chasing the American dream is often fueled by fear of, like, 'I'm going to get more.

302
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,000
 I need to accumulate more. I need to have enough so that I can retire.

303
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 I need to have enough to pay for kids. I need to have enough so that I can get married.'

304
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 And Jesus says, 'Those all are ingrained with the lie that you are the source of provision in your life,

305
00:16:53,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 and that will create anxiety. Living for the American dream makes you anxious.'"

306
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 This is why the man in the story is driven to go to Jesus and take his one shot with the Son of God

307
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,000
 and say, "Jesus, the heaven and hell stuff, that's great.

308
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:15,000
 Hey, will you tell my brother to give me some money?" Fear drives us.

309
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:21,000
 Often, fear of not being seen as successful creates an anxiety that,

310
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 "I'm not living up to other people's opinions or the standards or where I should be

311
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:29,000
 or where, you know, my friends are in this stage of life."

312
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:37,000
 And Jesus is saying, "Living for some version of what the world says is success is foolish,

313
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,000
 and it will make you anxious."

314
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:44,000
 The second idea is that living for the American dream will make you anxious.

315
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:49,000
 And Jesus says, "The solution to your anxiety is not more money.

316
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:57,000
 It is a deeper understanding of who your God is, how he has promised, 'I will provide for you.'

317
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,000
 I will ultimately provide for you on the cross where I gave my life for your greatest needs.'"

318
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 That's what Christians believe if you're not a follower of Jesus.

319
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,000
 They don't believe good people go to heaven, bad people go to hell.

320
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 They believe Jesus went through hell for us so that we wouldn't have to.

321
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,000
 He came to earth, died in our place as the payment for our sin,

322
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 and then he rose from the dead showing the payment cleared.

323
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 It was more than enough. That's what Christians believe.

324
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:24,000
 And he not only provided there, Jesus says, "And God will provide for your needs."

325
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,000
 Not for the path of success that you want, not for everything that you want in life,

326
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,000
 but he will provide for your needs. You can trust him.

327
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 And if you chase after, "I need to accomplish and succeed and live up to what everybody says," is the goal.

328
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:42,000
 It's a recipe for being anxious because living for the American dream just creates anxiety.

329
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:48,000
 As one great poet, Biggie, said, "More money, more problems."

330
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:52,000
 And we think it's a solution, and Jesus says, "It's not a solution.

331
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:56,000
 You can have everything that everyone else wants and be miserable."

332
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,000
 This is a girl named Chelsea Crist.

333
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:03,000
 Chelsea was Miss USA in 2019.

334
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 She was a lawyer who also had her MBA.

335
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:13,000
 She was a model, D1 athlete at one point in time, incredibly successful, top 10 in Miss Universe,

336
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:18,000
 was on Extra as a TV correspondent. She was an Emmy nominated.

337
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:23,000
 And 10 days ago, she took her life.

338
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
 She's beautiful.

339
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 Everything the world would say matters.

340
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 Everything you would want, and it didn't satisfy.

341
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 It created angst, anxiety, depression.

342
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:53,000
 Because everything the world says matters, you can't fill the part of your soul that was made by God for God.

343
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 And pursuing some version of success and what everyone says,

344
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 "This is the goal, and this is the car, and these are the clothes, and this is the way to look,

345
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,000
 this is the number of followers, and this is the house to have."

346
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:10,000
 It can't fulfill the part of you that only God can.

347
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 And you can either spend your life chasing and striving after that,

348
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 only to arrive at the epitome of what everyone would say is success and find it doesn't.

349
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 Or you can look to the one source that can, which is Jesus and a relationship of walking in line with him.

350
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:36,000
 I've been doing this a long time, and I have seen how chasing the American dream has left young adults empty,

351
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 their families empty. I've sat with young adults in tears who have more money than I will ever have,

352
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 who don't have to work at all, and they, through tears, cry out how money destroyed my family.

353
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 And the temptation for us is, you know, we're young adults, you're poor, you're like, "I got college debt."

354
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:59,000
 You're like, "You know, I bet we could handle it."

355
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:05,000
 And the truth is, money is not a solution for your anxiety.

356
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:09,000
 It's not a solution for the biggest needs and biggest problems that you have.

357
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:14,000
 Money is not a bad thing, but it doesn't offer you what Jesus can,

358
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:20,000
 which is a solution for that hole that exists in every heart and every person,

359
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 that no amount of status, success, home can ever fulfill.

360
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 And he says, "You can trust your Father to provide."

361
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 Living for the American dream makes you anxious.

362
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:36,000
 Living for eternity will give you peace.

363
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:41,000
 And then Jesus goes into the next portion of the text that tells us what I think is

364
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:44,000
 maybe the most tragic portion of this entire thing.

365
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:49,000
 He says, "Do not be afraid, little flock."

366
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:52,000
 It's pretty tender language.

367
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:56,000
 I mean, you know the scene. He's sitting there in front of this audience.

368
00:21:56,000 --> 00:22:01,000
 Man just chimes up from the crowd, and Jesus is like, "Man, let me talk about this,

369
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:03,000
 because this is going to be a big pitfall for a lot of people.

370
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 They're going to chase and seek something and accumulating or getting stuff.

371
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,000
 It's not going to work."

372
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:16,000
 And then he ends with, "So don't be afraid.

373
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:20,000
 Your Father is pleased to give you the kingdom.

374
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:23,000
 Sell your possessions and give to the poor.

375
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Provide purses for yourselves that will not wear out.

376
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:33,000
 A treasure in heaven that will never fail,

377
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:37,000
 where no thief can come near it and steal, no moth could ever make it destroy.

378
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:42,000
 For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also."

379
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 He says, "When you begin to live for eternity, something begins to shift in your heart.

380
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:50,000
 And when you live just for this life, something happens,

381
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 and at the end of this life, it will leave you eternally bankrupt.

382
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:56,000
 Perhaps the greatest tragedy of the American dream is it makes you only focus

383
00:22:56,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 and get so narrow focused on this life and leaves you eternally bankrupt."

384
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,000
 The third idea from the text we see is living for this life only

385
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:10,000
 or living for the American dream leaves you bankrupt.

386
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:16,000
 He introduces to a topic of I think why Jesus is so passionate about money.

387
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 He says there's a relationship between money and what you treasure and your heart.

388
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:26,000
 Do you know that Jesus, more than anybody else in the Bible, talks about money?

389
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 2,000 verses, he talks about money.

390
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 He talks about it more than he talks about heaven and hell combined.

391
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:37,000
 Why? Because Jesus wants you to be poor and he's against money? No.

392
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 Because he knows more than anything else in this life,

393
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:44,000
 money competes to sit on the throne of your heart,

394
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:49,000
 to make you feel a sense of control, security, peace,

395
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:54,000
 can distract you like nothing else or like few other things away from God

396
00:23:54,000 --> 00:24:00,000
 and build you up and make you think through pride you created what you have.

397
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 Jesus isn't against money. He doesn't want your money to have you.

398
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,000
 It's not against you having money.

399
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 And nothing like it competes for your heart.

400
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 Verses on prayer are 500. There's four times as many verses on money.

401
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 Because Jesus knows nothing in this life competes for your heart like wealth.

402
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:29,000
 Which means living in America, the wealthiest country on the planet,

403
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:32,000
 and living in cities like this or in suburbs or in affluent areas like Scottsdale

404
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,000
 and like Boise and like Dallas and like Austin

405
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:38,000
 and like all the different locations listening in right now,

406
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:43,000
 is one of the most dangerous places you can be for your faith.

407
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 Because nothing according to Jesus, where your treasure is, your heart will be also.

408
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:49,000
 In other words, your heart's going to follow wherever your treasure is.

409
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 It's competing for your heart like money.

410
00:24:53,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 And we live in a world that is unbelievably inundated in wealth

411
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 and how much you don't have and what you need.

412
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 There was a friend that was on staff a few years ago. His name was Paul.

413
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,000
 And he moved his family to West Dallas.

414
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:13,000
 And if you're listening, that's just a poorer area or higher poverty area of Dallas.

415
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,000
 And certainly was at the time, 10 years ago.

416
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
 And somebody asked him the question. He had kids.

417
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:24,000
 And he said, "Aren't you concerned about it not being that safe?"

418
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:29,000
 And he responded with something that I don't think I'll ever forget.

419
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,000
 And it was so convicting.

420
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:38,000
 You think the affluent suburbs are safe?

421
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:42,000
 You think living in some of the wealthiest areas in the country are safe?

422
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:45,000
 You think raising kids around all the environments where everyone has a Range Rover

423
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 and the amount of drugs that they'll introduce, do you think that's safe?

424
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,000
 No.

425
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:57,000
 It's every bit as dangerous as being in a place that has a higher crime rate.

426
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:01,000
 It's just a different type of danger. And it may even be worse.

427
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:05,000
 And Jesus would say, "You and I are to be on guard

428
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:09,000
 because nothing competes for your heart like money,

429
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:13,000
 like getting more stuff, like having more,

430
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:15,000
 more clothes, the right car."

431
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 And it does something to our heart.

432
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 And he also gives us an invitation that, "Hey, anything you invest for my kingdom

433
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,000
 will last for all of eternity."

434
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,000
 He's not trying to get you away from having nice things.

435
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:32,000
 He's trying to get you to see life in a right perspective,

436
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:34,000
 to see your world, to see the opportunity,

437
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:41,000
 to see your 20s, your 30s, your life in a right perspective.

