00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:04,000
 There's one from the Hubble Telescope

470
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:06,000
 where formerly it was out of focus,

471
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:11,000
 and then those lenses just-- everything came into focus.

472
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:15,000
 This is what Jesus is attempting to do through his teaching.

473
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:18,000
 He's not telling them that, hey, you living a life where you have nice things,

474
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,000
 you have a good job, you get out of debt,

475
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,000
 or you have a car and you live in a house someday is bad things.

476
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:26,000
 What he is saying is you spending your life

477
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:28,000
 living for your kingdom, building into your kingdom,

478
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,000
 spending not just your 20s, I mean all of your life,

479
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:34,000
 investing in acquiring more stuff and having more things

480
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:37,000
 and having a life that everyone in the world says is successful

481
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:40,000
 is going to leave you eternally bankrupt.

482
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,000
 Yet you spending your life investing in my kingdom,

483
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,000
 serving and sharing in my kingdom

484
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:48,000
 is going to leave you eternally with treasures that will never fade,

485
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,000
 a reward that cannot be taken from you.

486
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:53,000
 Nothing you invest in this life can be taken.

487
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:57,000
 And candidly, my fear, because this generation just haven't done this for a while,

488
00:28:57,000 --> 00:29:02,000
 there is a higher level of materialism

489
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:05,000
 in young adults today,

490
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:10,000
 in the church today,

491
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:13,000
 than just a few years ago there were.

492
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,000
 And I don't know what happened, and I certainly--

493
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:18,000
 it's been a challenge for me this week

494
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 addressing what happened.

495
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,000
 Maybe it was social media and the fact that everything everyone wears

496
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:26,000
 gets posted everywhere and there's all this pressure to look some certain way.

497
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:29,000
 And it's like the church all of a sudden shifted from this radical, reckless,

498
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 whatever you want from me, Jesus, take it all.

499
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,000
 I'll give anything and everything. I want to live for your kingdom.

500
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,000
 I'm not living for what other people think

501
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 and what car that I drive and the house that I have.

502
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 I want to live for you.

503
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:46,000
 It's like that has shrunk in the hearts of your people.

504
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 And not all of them.

505
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,000
 There are men and women who,

506
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,000
 just like that Hubble telescope,

507
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,000
 they see things in perspective.

508
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,000
 They see life. They see our world more clearly.

509
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:59,000
 And this life more clearly.

510
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 And they're not giving their 20s, they're not giving themselves

511
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:04,000
 to living for a kingdom that's going to fade, which is theirs.

512
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 Which is any kingdom that is not Jesus.

513
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 Think about this man's question

514
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,000
 and how narrow focus he is.

515
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:16,000
 I'm about to land the plane.

516
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:20,000
 He's standing in front of the son of God.

517
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 He's got a shot to talk to Jesus.

518
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 Very few people who ever lived got that shot.

519
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:30,000
 Think about how small and petty what he asked for is.

520
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:33,000
 How much was the inheritance?

521
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 Five grand, which would have been enormous in that day and age.

522
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,000
 And he's standing before Jesus, he's like,

523
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 "Jesus, I want you to come with me, come to my house,

524
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 "and I want you to talk to my brother."

525
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:47,000
 In the same way, think about how small

526
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 the perspective of living for the American dream,

527
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 that, "Hey, I'm going to get the car, good, get the car,

528
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,000
 "then what? Then I'm going to get the house, good,

529
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,000
 "you got the house, then what?

530
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 "Oh, I got to have the spouse, okay, you got the spouse,

531
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 "then what? Then we're going to have kids, okay, then what?

532
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 "Then I'm going to have a golden retriever,

533
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:03,000
 "and then I'm going to retire, then what?"

534
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 You think that's going to fill anything?

535
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 Are you really going to give your life to something

536
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 that's going to fade, that doesn't satisfy,

537
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 that story after story after story tells you,

538
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 and Jesus, on the planet, says,

539
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 "You are wasting your life."

540
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 Or, are you going to use the gifts God has given you,

541
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,000
 the time God has given you, the finances God has given you,

542
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 the story God has given you, to say,

543
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 "I am going to live for Jesus and my generation.

544
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 "I want to go all in with you, Christ, use my life.

545
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 "Take me and use me as a force in a really dark world for you.

546
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 "I want to make your name great, not my name great."

547
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 And in doing so, Jesus says,

548
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 "Invest in the only kingdom that will last, which is his."

549
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 In conclusion, living for the American dream

550
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 leaves you bankrupt eternally.

551
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:01,000
 Living for eternity leaves you rich.

552
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:04,000
 Living for the American dream makes you a fool.

553
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:08,000
 Living for eternity will make you filled and full.

554
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 Living for the American dream makes you anxious.

555
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:15,000
 But living in light of eternity with the God of eternity

556
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,000
 brings you peace.

557
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 That snowman, because we're in Texas,

558
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:27,000
 something happens when two days later it's 70 degrees.

559
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:30,000
 It goes away.

560
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 And all that snow and all that was created, it's gone.

561
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 Let me tell you my biggest fear for this room.

562
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:44,000
 That snowman is a picture for how many people spend their life.

563
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:47,000
 They work and they build, they create, they mass,

564
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:50,000
 they get their house, get the job, build the company,

565
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,000
 put it all together.

566
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:59,000
 And just like the snowman, when the sun comes back, it's gone.

567
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 And when the sun comes back, the son of God,

568
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:08,000
 you will have built a kingdom that will not last,

569
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 invested your life in something Jesus said is foolish.

570
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 Not 'cause he's against you having nice things.

571
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:19,000
 He's against things having you and you giving your life to them.

572
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:23,000
 And so we rest in peace to the American dream

573
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:26,000
 'cause you were made for something far bigger and far greater

574
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
 and are put on this planet for a purpose to know God,

575
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 to make him known, to not waste your life building snowmen

576
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:36,000
 that will fade, but to build a kingdom.

577
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 The Bible says it's unshakable, that will last for all of eternity

578
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,000
 for those who know him.

579
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 And anything they built towards that will last for all of eternity.

580
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 Let me pray.

581
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 Father, I pray that you would unleash in our generation

582
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 men and women who serve you and live for you with reckless abandon.

583
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 They wouldn't get caught up and distracted in the temptations

584
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 of the cities and places and spaces we live in.

585
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:07,000
 Of all the things the world says, this is what success is,

586
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 this is what matters.

587
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 And for that to happen, God, we need your help.

588
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:14,000
 Would you take ground in our heart, the places in our heart

589
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,000
 that run after the things of this world,

590
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:22,000
 that seek security in things that ultimately can't provide it,

591
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:25,000
 that find our identity or our worth or find peace in things

592
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:31,000
 that are fleeting, and we'd find them in you,

593
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 and we would live radically for you.

594
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 Thank you, dear God, who radically gave his life for us

595
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 so that anyone who trusts in Jesus would spend all of eternity

596
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:45,000
 with him in the only kingdom that will last, his.

597
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 We worship you now in song.

598
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 Amen.

